---
---

<section id="wedge" class="wedge">
  <hr class="hairline" />
  <div class="wedge-inner">

    <p class="mono file-marker">02 / THE WEDGE</p>

    <p class="wedge-line">
      We don't charge to find the <span class="marked">leaks</span>.
      We charge to fix them.
    </p>

    <p class="context">
      INKZ runs forensic audits of small-business operations. Free diagnostic, two to three weeks,
      no obligation. If we find what we think we will find, we propose a bespoke engagement to fix
      it. If not, you keep the report.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .wedge {
    padding: var(--space-32) var(--space-8);
  }

  .wedge .hairline {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-32);
  }

  .wedge-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-body-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .file-marker {
    color: var(--graphite-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .wedge-line {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--type-900);
    font-weight: var(--weight-medium);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  /* Forensic-red first appearance: marker underline on "leaks".
     The diagnostic identifies the leaks. This word is the exhibit.
     4px solid bar, flush under the baseline, no gap.
     Appears exactly once. Nowhere else in this component. */
  .marked {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--forensic);
    text-decoration-thickness: 4px;
    text-underline-offset: 0.08em;
  }

  .context {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--type-400);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--graphite);
    max-width: 52ch;
  }

  /* On smaller screens, drop to type-700 so the mono line still breathes */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .wedge-line {
      font-size: var(--type-800);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .wedge {
      padding: var(--space-24) var(--space-6);
    }

    .wedge .hairline {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-24);
    }

    .wedge-line {
      font-size: var(--type-700);
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }

    .context {
      font-size: var(--type-300);
    }
  }
</style>
